class Solution {
    public int minAddToMakeValid(String s) {
        int res = 0, balance = 0;
        for (char c : s.toCharArray()) {
            balance += c == '(' ? 1 : -1;
            if (balance < 0) {
                res++;
                balance++;
            }
        }
        return res + balance;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: This solution uses a single pass through the string, maintaining a balance of open and close parentheses. When the balance becomes negative, a close parenthesis is added, and when the balance is positive at the end, open parentheses are added.

